# CronJob history limits (BimRoss)

When adding or editing **`batch/v1` CronJob** resources in **`rancher-admin`** (or matching GitOps repos), set:

- **`successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 1`** — keep exactly one last successful run visible for “it completed” confidence in Rancher/`kubectl`.
- **`failedJobsHistoryLimit: 1`** — keep exactly one last failure for debugging without a pile of Completed/Failed pods.

Do **not** default to `0`/`0` unless there is a documented exception (e.g. paired with aggressive **`ttlSecondsAfterFinished`** and an explicit reason to leave no Job record).

If a workload needs more failure history for triage, bump **`failedJobsHistoryLimit`** in that manifest only and note why in the PR.
